### Trace demo prerequisites
# Start the application locally.
# With Spring Boot Docker Compose support enabled, `compose.yaml` will start:
# - PostgreSQL
# - Zipkin at http://localhost:9411
#
# These requests exercise the local trace demo endpoints:
# - /trace/1 shows the current request trace information
# - /trace/n recursively calls /trace/(n-1) down to /trace/1
#
# Use the Zipkin UI to inspect the resulting spans.

### 1. Call /trace/1 without an inbound traceparent
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/1

### 2. Call /trace/1 with a fixed W3C traceparent header
# The response should show this trace ID, and the log line should include the same traceId/spanId.
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/1
traceparent: 00-4bf92f3577b34da6a3ce929d0e0e4736-00f067aa0ba902b7-01

### 3. Call /trace/3 with a fixed W3C traceparent header
# The response should include:
# - top-level trace details for /trace/3
# - nested downstream details for /trace/2 and /trace/1
# - the same traceId across all calls
# - different spanIds for each downstream call
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/3
traceparent: 00-4bf92f3577b34da6a3ce929d0e0e4736-00f067aa0ba902b7-01

### 4. Call /trace/10 to generate a deeper span chain
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/10
traceparent: 00-4bf92f3577b34da6a3ce929d0e0e4736-00f067aa0ba902b7-01

### 5. Invalid values return HTTP 400
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/0

###
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/11

###
GET http://localhost:8080/trace/not-a-number

### 6. Open the Zipkin UI
GET http://localhost:9411/zipkin/
